summary: Frontend-only testing of LAUTECH Rentals platform after migration to Supabase. All key pages render correctly. Build succeeds. No old backend API references found. Supabase credentials are placeholders (MOCKED), so data operations fail but UI works.
passed_tests: Home page loads with hero section (Find Your Perfect Student Accommodation)
Home page shows stats section (500+, 1,000+, 50+, 24/7)
Home page shows features section (Why Choose LAUTECH Rentals)
Home page shows CTA section (Ready to Find Your New Home)
Browse Properties button visible on home page
Get Started button visible for unauthenticated users
Browse page loads with search bar
Browse page has filter toggle button
Browse page filter panel shows Property Type and Price Range filters
Browse page Apply Filters and Reset buttons work
Login page renders with email and password fields
Login page has Submit button
Login page form fields are interactive
Register page renders with name, email, password, confirm password fields
Register page has Submit button
Register page form fields are interactive
Desktop navigation shows Home, Browse, Login, Register links for unauthenticated users
Mobile bottom navigation shows Home, Browse, Login, Register
Mobile menu toggle opens dropdown with Login/Register buttons
Mobile navigation clicking works (tested Browse)
Build succeeds without errors (yarn build)
No axios or /api/ or localhost:8001 references in code
vercel.json exists with SPA rewrite rules
.nvmrc set to Node 20

mocked_integrations.note: MOCKED - Supabase credentials are placeholder values
mocked_integrations.expected_behavior: Data fetching fails with 'Failed to load properties' error - this is expected

critical_code_review_comments: ESLint warnings for missing dependencies in useEffect hooks (AdminDashboard, AgentDashboard, Browse, BuyTokens, Profile, PropertyDetails) - minor, not blocking
Supabase URL in .env has quotes which may cause issues: should be REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co (without quotes)

success_rate.frontend: 100% - All UI elements render and are interactive

context_for_next_testing_agent: This is a frontend-only React app connecting to Supabase. Supabase credentials are placeholders so all data operations will fail. Backend exists but is not used by this app. All pages render correctly. To test with real data, configure real Supabase project credentials in frontend/.env (REACT_APP_SUPABASE_URL and REACT_APP_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY without quotes).
